# Shelf 3D Bookmark Manager - Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values

# =============================================================================
# GitHub OAuth Configuration (Required for Cloud Sync)
# =============================================================================

# GitHub OAuth App Client ID
# Get this from: https://github.com/settings/developers
# Create a new OAuth App and copy the Client ID here
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=Ov23li38mBQ1KmiGQYn1

# GitHub OAuth App Client Secret
# Get this from: https://github.com/settings/developers
# Copy the Client Secret from your GitHub OAuth App
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=f89636b75ce688b03f797a8251619e7ba9f5418c


# =============================================================================
# NextAuth Configuration (Required for Authentication)
# =============================================================================

# NextAuth Secret - Generate a random string for production
# You can generate one at: https://generate-secret.vercel.app/32
# Or use: openssl rand -base64 32
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=cca0635c34dc908161f5bb3a267579af

# NextAuth URL - Your application's base URL
# Development: http://localhost:3001
# Production: https://your-domain.com
NEXTAUTH_URL=https://shelf-bri.pages.dev/

# =============================================================================
# Application Configuration (Optional)
# =============================================================================

# Application Environment
# Values: development, staging, production
NODE_ENV=development

# Application Port (Optional - defaults to 3000)
# PORT=3001

# =============================================================================
# Database Configuration (Optional - if you add database support later)
# =============================================================================

# Database URL (if using a database in the future)
# DATABASE_URL=your_database_connection_string

# =============================================================================
# Third-party Services (Optional)
# =============================================================================

# Analytics Configuration (Optional)
# ANALYTICS_ID=your_analytics_tracking_id

# Error Tracking (Optional)
# SENTRY_DSN=your_sentry_dsn

# =============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env.local:
#    cp .env.local.example .env.local

# 2. Create a GitHub OAuth App:
#    - Go to https://github.com/settings/developers
#    - Click "New OAuth App"
#    - Fill in the application details:
#      * Application name: Shelf 3D Bookmark Manager
#      * Homepage URL: http://localhost:3001 (or your domain)
#      * Authorization callback URL: http://localhost:3001/api/auth/github/callback
#    - Copy the Client ID and Client Secret to this file

# 3. Generate a NextAuth Secret:
#    - Visit https://generate-secret.vercel.app/32
#    - Or run: openssl rand -base64 32
#    - Copy the generated secret to NEXTAUTH_SECRET

# 4. Update NEXTAUTH_URL:
#    - For development: http://localhost:3001
#    - For production: https://your-actual-domain.com

# 5. Restart your development server:
#    npm run dev

# =============================================================================
# Production Deployment Notes
# =============================================================================

# When deploying to production (Vercel, Netlify, etc.):
# 1. Update NEXTAUTH_URL to your production domain
# 2. Update GitHub OAuth App callback URL to:
#    https://your-domain.com/api/auth/github/callback
# 3. Set all environment variables in your hosting platform
# 4. Never commit .env.local to version control

# =============================================================================
# Security Notes
# =============================================================================

# - Never commit .env.local or actual environment variables to Git
# - Use different OAuth Apps for development and production
# - Rotate secrets regularly in production
# - Use strong, unique secrets for each environment
# - Restrict OAuth App access to necessary scopes only

# =============================================================================
# Troubleshooting
# =============================================================================

# If GitHub OAuth is not working:
# 1. Check that GITHUB_CLIENT_ID and GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET are correct
# 2. Verify the callback URL matches exactly (including http/https)
# 3. Ensure the OAuth App is not suspended
# 4. Check browser console for error messages
# 5. Verify NEXTAUTH_SECRET is set and not empty

# If sync is not working:
# 1. Check GitHub API rate limits
# 2. Verify the user has granted gist scope
# 3. Check network connectivity
# 4. Look for error messages in browser dev tools

# For more help, check the documentation or create an issue at:
# https://github.com/your-username/shelf-bookmark-manager/issues